author: gstein
msg: Rearrange some of the (loggy) operations within close_file() to minimize
the use of a log_accum to delay certain changes relative to others.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/update_editor.c:
(merge_file): take an ENTRY parameter, rather than fetching it ourself.
remove the associated ERR_UNVERSIONED_RESOURCE.
(construct_base_node): new helper function to hack in a BASE node,
ripped out of close_file.
(close_file): fetch the ENTRY before anything starts mucking around with
changing nodes. move the BASE node construction as early as possible.
the ->added and ->add_existed checks are constant in this function, so
there is no need to wait. once we have LAST_CHANGE, then shove that
into the BASE node. once the NEW_*_PROPS values have been computed,
then get those installed right away. at that point, it *should* be
possible to flush DELAYED_LOG_ACCUM, but there is a bad interaction
somewhere, so that isn't done until after merge_file() is called. pass
the earlier-read ENTRY into merge_file().
